snippet.title: Live Coding: File Forensics with Rust
snippet.description:
Let's try out some basic file forensics with Rust. Let's see how many of these tasks we can knock out in one sitting:
- Getting timestamp/size/permissions of a file
- Dumping file as hex
- Looking for ASCII characters
- Looking for file signatures
- Looking for large files
- Looking for recently changed files
- Exif data
- Steganography
